Reasoning: The paper focuses on visual recognition models and their performance in semi-supervised learning, specifically in the areas of human keypoint detection and general object detection. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for ensembling predictions from multiple transformations of unlabeled data, which falls under the umbrella of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the potential for surpassing state-of-the-art fully supervised methods, which could be relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
